{{Quote|Admiral! Lock down the hyperspace rings! Hurry!|[[Anakin Skywalker]], to [[Wullf Yularen]]|<ref name="Children of the Force" />}}
The '''hyperspace transport ring''', also known as a '''hyperdrive ring''',<ref name="The Glass Abyss">''[[Mace Windu: The Glass Abyss]]''</ref> was a device that provided [[hyperspace]] travel capabilities to [[starfighter]]s with no on-board [[hyperdrive]], such as the [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor|Delta-7]]<ref name="AotC">{{Film|II}}</ref> and [[Delta-7B Aethersprite-class light interceptor|7B ''Aethersprite''-class light interceptor]]s,<ref name="Downfall">{{TCW|Downfall of a Droid}}</ref> and the [[V-19 Torrent starfighter]].<ref name="Children of the Force" /> The [[Syliure-31 hyperspace docking ring]] was one such [[transport]] ring.<ref name="AEYNTK">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref> The [[hyperframe]] was a similar technology used during the [[High Republic Era]].<ref>''[[The High Republic: The Rising Storm]]''</ref>

[[Darth]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Vader's]] personal [[Alpha-3 Nimbus-class V-wing starfighter|V-wing]] [[squadron]] used hyperspace rings during a pursuit of weapon hijackers from [[Cham Syndulla]]'s [[Free Ryloth Movement]].<ref name="Lords of the Sith" />

During the [[New Republic Era]], [[Morgan Elsbeth]]'s [[Morgan Elsbeth's forces|forces]] constructed the ''[[Eye of Sion]]'', a prototype hyperdrive ring hundreds of times larger than a typical one and, according to [[architect droid]] [[Huyang]], powerful enough to complete [[extragalactic]] journeys, in order to retrieve [[Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo|Thrawn]] from his [[Exile (punishment)|exile]].<ref name="Part 3" />

